Patch Set 6: Workflow-1

Steven, thank you very much for your review. The code looks much better after it!
For now I think we can set WIP status and left the docstring and the commit message as-is until your spec will be approved.

Patch Set 6: Code-Review-2

We most likely need another version bump given this change. Let's chat offline sometime after meetup.

Patch Set 6:

What do you mean by version bump? v3?

Patch Set 6:

We need a spec for this (sorry about this late addition). A change like this needs to be well documented and communicated with the operators.

Version bump meaning minor version bump. There may be some more patches which call for a minor version bump so, let's c-ordinate with them.

Patch Set 6:

FYI ... API working group guidelines for sorting have merged:

https://github.com/openstack/api-wg/blob/master/guidelines/pagination_filter_sort.rst

Patch Set 6:

Thanks for that Steven!

I think we still would need something for Glance for documenting these related changes to avoid keeping operators, users, patrons etc. clueless :)

Patch Set 6:

I'm happy to write up a spec for these changes in glance and glanceclient if no one else has the time.

Patch Set 6:

Ian: that would be a great. I think we need to move ahead on this change soon.

Patch Set 6:

Hey! I didn't look here for a long time.It's a great news! I will have some time to write a spec near the end of the week, so I can do it or share this work with Ian.
